</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte" pageId="25" pageNumber="86" pagination="79 - 88" title="Neue Eintagsfliegen der Gattungen Epeorus und Iron aus dem Himalaja (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae)." volume="50" year="2006 b">Braasch (2006b)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on larval specimens from River Indravati near Dalaghat 1,200 m, Nepal, Himalayas. In this study, this species were found from northern and northeastern parts of Thailand. This species is different from other known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
by abdominal terga 2-9 each with single, prominent, and acute median spine.
</paragraph>
